&lt;p&gt;At Fay, our mission is to make nutrition a foundational pillar of preventative care, improving outcomes, accessibility, and affordability at scale. We&#39;re building AI-powered infrastructure to transform preventative healthcare. Think that&#39;s bold? We&#39;re just getting started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, Fay is a three-sided marketplace connecting providers, patients, and payers to revolutionize preventative care delivery. Our b2b2c business-in-a-box solution empowers dietitians to deliver high-quality, affordable nutrition care, helps patients take control of their health, and enables payers to build healthier member populations. Nutrition is our starting point, not the finish line. The platform we&#39;re building will expand into new areas of preventative health and wellness as we grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re proud to be one of the fastest-growing companies in healthtech, backed by category-defining investors like General Catalyst, Forerunner, 1984, and Goldman Sachs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to leverage AI-driven technology to transform preventative care and make a real-world impact on health? Let&#39;s talk.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;This Business Operations role sits at the center of Fay&#39;s three-sided marketplace — payers, providers, and members — and the flywheel that connects clinical quality, payer trust, provider economics, and member retention. It works across Member Experience, Provider Operations &amp;amp; Growth, Clinical Operations, and Payer Operations, flexing toward whichever side of the marketplace needs the most attention at any given time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;This is a strategic, analytical role grounded in operations. You&#39;ll own data and insights that drive decision-making, build a strong understanding of supply and demand dynamics across payers, providers, and members, and translate those insights into clear, actionable recommendations. You&#39;ll also help build and maintain the operating systems that keep a fast-moving, complex organization aligned and executing effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;At Fay, we value people who are adaptable, resourceful, and excited to tackle new challenges as the business evolves. Priorities in this role will shift as the business does — one quarter you might be deep in payer economics, the next focused on provider supply, the next on member retention. We&#39;re looking for someone who&#39;s energized by that kind of movement, comfortable getting hands-on wherever the highest-impact work is, and eager to apply their skills across the marketplace rather than in a single fixed lane.&lt;/p&gt;
